            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EWisdom%20is%20the%20most%20powerful%20force%20in%20the%20world-a%20force%20greater%20than%20riches%2C%20power%2C%20or%20long%20life.%20Solomon%20realized%20that%20without%20wisdom%20his%20youthfulness%20and%20lack%20of%20experience%20would%20quickly%20disqualify%20him%20from%20leading%20a%20nation%20of%20millions%20of%20people.%20He%20therefore%20asked%20God%2C%20%22Give%20me%20an%20understanding%20mind%20so%20that%20I%20can%20govern%20your%20people%20well%20and%20know%20the%20difference%20between%20right%20and%20wrong.%20For%20who%20by%20himself%20is%20able%20to%20govern%20this%20great%20nation%20of%20yours%3F%22%20(1%20Kings%203%3A9).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGod%20was%20pleased%20with%20Solomon's%20request%20and%20granted%20him%20not%20only%20wisdom%20but%20also%20riches%2C%20honor%2C%20and%20long%20life.%20Because%20of%20his%20great%20wisdom%2C%20the%20kings%20and%20queens%20of%20the%20entire%20earth%20came%20before%20Solomon's%20throne.%20His%20God-given%20wisdom%20enabled%20him%20to%20efficiently%20administrate%20the%20kingdom%20by%20using%20twelve%20district%20governors.%20Furthermore%2C%20he%20knew%20the%20solution%20to%20difficult%20problems%20of%20justice%20in%20civil%20disputes%20(v.%2028).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESolomon's%20wisdom%20extended%20into%20the%20natural%20world%2C%20too.%20%22He%20composed%20some%203%2C000%20proverbs%20and%20wrote%201%2C005%20songs.%20He%20could%20speak%20with%20authority%20about%20all%20kinds%20of%20plants%2C%20from%20the%20great%20cedar%20of%20Lebanon%20to%20the%20tiny%20hyssop%20that%20grows%20from%20cracks%20in%20a%20wall.%20He%20could%20also%20speak%20about%20animals%2C%20birds%2C%20reptiles%2C%20and%20fish%22%20(1%20Kings%204%3A32-33).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPeter%20and%20the%20apostles%20realized%20that%20if%20people%20were%20%22well%20respected%22%20and%20%22full%20of%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20and%20wisdom%22%20(Acts%206%3A3)%2C%20they%20could%20be%20placed%20in%20positions%20of%20responsibility.%20Today%2C%20in%20faith%2C%20ask%20God%20for%20wisdom%20to%20enter%20your%20heart.%20Then%20watch%20as%20He%20promotes%20you%20to%20new%20responsibility%20and%20privilege%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20both%20God%20and%20humanity!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
